
Next steps:
  1. Build Docker images: ./build-images.sh all
  2. Generate SSL certificates: ./generate-certs.sh
  3. Start base services: docker compose up -d
  4. Create instances:
     ./ssmd instance create --name v4-main --type v4 --subdomain v4
     ./ssmd instance create --name sh-main --type selfhosted --subdomain selfhosted
  5. Run database setup:
{% if services.orangescrum %}
     V2 DB: docker compose exec mysql mysql -uroot -prootpassword orangescrum < os-v2/your-dump.sql
{% endif %}
     ./ssmd instance db-setup --name v4-main
     ./ssmd instance db-setup --name sh-main

Instance Management:
  Create:   ./ssmd instance create --name <name> --type <v4|selfhosted> --subdomain <sub>
  List:     ./ssmd instance list
  Stop:     ./ssmd instance stop --name <name>
  Start:    ./ssmd instance start --name <name>
  Destroy:  ./ssmd instance destroy --name <name> --drop-db
  DB Setup: ./ssmd instance db-setup --name <name>
  Logs:     ./ssmd instance logs --name <name> -f
  Shell:    ./ssmd instance shell --name <name>

Access via VNC Browser:
  Open: http://localhost:3000

Controller Web UI:
  https://control.{{ domain }}  (credentials in .env: CONTROLLER_USER/CONTROLLER_PASS)

Access points (inside VNC browser):
{% for point in access_points %}
  - {{ point.name }}: {{ point.url }}
{% endfor %}

Host-exposed ports (see .env for values):
  - PostgreSQL, MySQL, Redis, Memcached — bound to 127.0.0.1
